 soldiers. Tubach powerfully provides new insights into Germany's most tragic years, offering a nuanced response to the abiding question of how a nation made the quantum leap from anti-Semitism to systematic genocide.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aNational socialismxSocial aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, German. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xPersonal narratives, German. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectsxGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszGermany. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948884423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520948884.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles